<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<p id="Par41" class="p">When the endowment of the rich gets larger than two times the poor’s (
 <italic class="italic">W</italic>
 <sub class="sub">R</sub> ≥ 2
 <italic class="italic">W</italic>
 <sub class="sub">P</sub>) the two best response curves Eqs. (
 <xref rid="Equ11" ref-type="" class="xref">11)</xref> and (
 <xref rid="Equ12" ref-type="" class="xref">12)</xref> do not intersect anymore. Now there are four regimes of 
 <italic class="italic">λ</italic>
 <sub class="sub">R</sub>. If the poor contribute nothing, 
 <italic class="italic">c</italic>
 <sub class="sub">P</sub> = 0, the best response of the rich is to give half of their wealth 
 <inline-formula id="IEq41" class="inline-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <tex-math id="M115" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$c_{\mathrm{R}}^ \ast = W_{\mathrm{R}}/2$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <math id="M116" class="math">
    <msubsup class="msubsup">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">c</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">R</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mo class="mo">*</mo>
     </mrow>
    </msubsup>
    <mo class="mo">=</mo>
    <msub class="msub">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">W</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">R</mi>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
    <mo class="mo">∕</mo>
    <mn class="mn">2</mn>
   </math>
   <inline-graphic xlink:href="41467_2018_4968_Article_IEq41.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </inline-formula> (Eq. (
 <xref rid="Equ11" ref-type="" class="xref">11)</xref>). According to the condition 
 <italic class="italic">W</italic>
 <sub class="sub">R</sub> ≥ 2
 <italic class="italic">W</italic>
 <sub class="sub">P</sub> the best response (Eq. (
 <xref rid="Equ12" ref-type="" class="xref">12)</xref>) for the poor is then 
 <inline-formula id="IEq42" class="inline-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <tex-math id="M117" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$c_{\mathrm{P}} = \left( {W_{\mathrm{P}} - c_{\mathrm{R}}^ \ast } \right)/2 \le 0$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <math id="M118" class="math">
    <msub class="msub">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">c</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">P</mi>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
    <mo class="mo">=</mo>
    <mfenced close=")" open="(" separators="" class="mfenced">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <msub class="msub">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">W</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">P</mi>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
      <mo class="mo">-</mo>
      <msubsup class="msubsup">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">c</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">R</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mo class="mo">*</mo>
       </mrow>
      </msubsup>
     </mrow>
    </mfenced>
    <mo class="mo">∕</mo>
    <mn class="mn">2</mn>
    <mo class="mo">≤</mo>
    <mn class="mn">0</mn>
   </math>
   <inline-graphic xlink:href="41467_2018_4968_Article_IEq42.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </inline-formula>. The poor player has no incentive to contribute and so the evolutionary stable state is 
 <inline-formula id="IEq43" class="inline-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <tex-math id="M119" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$c_{\mathrm{R}}^ \ast = W_{\mathrm{R}}/2$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <math id="M120" class="math">
    <msubsup class="msubsup">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">c</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">R</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mo class="mo">*</mo>
     </mrow>
    </msubsup>
    <mo class="mo">=</mo>
    <msub class="msub">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">W</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">R</mi>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
    <mo class="mo">∕</mo>
    <mn class="mn">2</mn>
   </math>
   <inline-graphic xlink:href="41467_2018_4968_Article_IEq43.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </inline-formula> and 
 <inline-formula id="IEq44" class="inline-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <tex-math id="M121" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$c_{\mathrm{P}}^ \ast = 0$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <math id="M122" class="math">
    <msubsup class="msubsup">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">c</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">P</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mo class="mo">*</mo>
     </mrow>
    </msubsup>
    <mo class="mo">=</mo>
    <mn class="mn">0</mn>
   </math>
   <inline-graphic xlink:href="41467_2018_4968_Article_IEq44.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </inline-formula> as long as the condition 
 <inline-formula id="IEq45" class="inline-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <tex-math id="M123" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$C &lt; \frac{W}{{\lambda _{\mathrm{R}}}}$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <math id="M124" class="math">
    <mi class="mi">C</mi>
    <mo class="mo">&lt;</mo>
    <mfrac class="mfrac">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">W</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <msub class="msub">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">λ</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">R</mi>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
     </mrow>
    </mfrac>
   </math>
   <inline-graphic xlink:href="41467_2018_4968_Article_IEq45.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </inline-formula> or (with 
 <italic class="italic">C</italic> = 
 <italic class="italic">W</italic>
 <sub class="sub">R</sub>/2) 
 <inline-formula id="IEq46" class="inline-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <tex-math id="M125" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$\lambda _{\mathrm{R}} &lt; 2\frac{W}{{W_{\mathrm{R}}}}$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <math id="M126" class="math">
    <msub class="msub">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">λ</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">R</mi>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
    <mo class="mo">&lt;</mo>
    <mn class="mn">2</mn>
    <mfrac class="mfrac">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">W</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <msub class="msub">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">W</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">R</mi>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
     </mrow>
    </mfrac>
   </math>
   <inline-graphic xlink:href="41467_2018_4968_Article_IEq46.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </inline-formula> is fulfilled. As 
 <italic class="italic">λ</italic>
 <sub class="sub">R</sub> increases to 
 <inline-formula id="IEq47" class="inline-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <tex-math id="M127" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$\lambda _{\mathrm{R}} \ge 2\frac{W}{{W_{\mathrm{R}}}}$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <math id="M128" class="math">
    <msub class="msub">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">λ</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">R</mi>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
    <mo class="mo">≥</mo>
    <mn class="mn">2</mn>
    <mfrac class="mfrac">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">W</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <msub class="msub">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">W</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">R</mi>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
     </mrow>
    </mfrac>
   </math>
   <inline-graphic xlink:href="41467_2018_4968_Article_IEq47.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </inline-formula> the risk for the rich becomes 0 and we cannot calculate the best response. The rich now contribute as little as possible to just about fulfill this condition of zero risk (
 <inline-formula id="IEq48" class="inline-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <tex-math id="M129" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$c_{\mathrm{R}}^ \ast = \frac{W}{{\lambda _{\mathrm{R}}}}$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <math id="M130" class="math">
    <msubsup class="msubsup">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">c</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">R</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mo class="mo">*</mo>
     </mrow>
    </msubsup>
    <mo class="mo">=</mo>
    <mfrac class="mfrac">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">W</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <msub class="msub">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">λ</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">R</mi>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
     </mrow>
    </mfrac>
   </math>
   <inline-graphic xlink:href="41467_2018_4968_Article_IEq48.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </inline-formula>, see Eq. (
 <xref rid="Equ5" ref-type="" class="xref">5)</xref>) and the poor still pay nothing as long as 
 <inline-formula id="IEq49" class="inline-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <tex-math id="M131" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$c_{\mathrm{R}}^ \ast &gt; W_{\mathrm{P}}$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <math id="M132" class="math">
    <msubsup class="msubsup">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">c</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">R</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mo class="mo">*</mo>
     </mrow>
    </msubsup>
    <mo class="mo">&gt;</mo>
    <msub class="msub">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">W</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">P</mi>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
   </math>
   <inline-graphic xlink:href="41467_2018_4968_Article_IEq49.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </inline-formula> (Eq. (
 <xref rid="Equ12" ref-type="" class="xref">12)</xref>). Once that threshold is met, which is equivalent to 
 <inline-formula id="IEq50" class="inline-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <tex-math id="M133" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$\lambda _{\mathrm{R}} \ge \frac{W}{{W_{\mathrm{P}}}}$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <math id="M134" class="math">
    <msub class="msub">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">λ</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">R</mi>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
    <mo class="mo">≥</mo>
    <mfrac class="mfrac">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">W</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <msub class="msub">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">W</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">P</mi>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
     </mrow>
    </mfrac>
   </math>
   <inline-graphic xlink:href="41467_2018_4968_Article_IEq50.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </inline-formula>, the best response function for the poor (Eq. (
 <xref rid="Equ12" ref-type="" class="xref">12)</xref>) starts to matter and solving for this and the threshold condition (Eq. (
 <xref rid="Equ5" ref-type="" class="xref">5)</xref>) results in the optimal strategies 
 <inline-formula id="IEq51" class="inline-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <tex-math id="M135" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$c_{\mathrm{R}}^ \ast = 2\frac{W}{{\lambda _{\mathrm{R}}}} - W_{\mathrm{P}}$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <math id="M136" class="math">
    <msubsup class="msubsup">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">c</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">R</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mo class="mo">*</mo>
     </mrow>
    </msubsup>
    <mo class="mo">=</mo>
    <mn class="mn">2</mn>
    <mfrac class="mfrac">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">W</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <msub class="msub">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">λ</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">R</mi>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
     </mrow>
    </mfrac>
    <mo class="mo">-</mo>
    <msub class="msub">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">W</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">P</mi>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
   </math>
   <inline-graphic xlink:href="41467_2018_4968_Article_IEq51.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </inline-formula> and 
 <inline-formula id="IEq52" class="inline-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <tex-math id="M137" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$c_{\mathrm{P}}^ \ast = W_{\mathrm{P}} - \frac{W}{{\lambda _{\mathrm{R}}}}$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <math id="M138" class="math">
    <msubsup class="msubsup">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">c</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">P</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mo class="mo">*</mo>
     </mrow>
    </msubsup>
    <mo class="mo">=</mo>
    <msub class="msub">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">W</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">P</mi>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
    <mo class="mo">-</mo>
    <mfrac class="mfrac">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">W</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <msub class="msub">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">λ</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">R</mi>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
     </mrow>
    </mfrac>
   </math>
   <inline-graphic xlink:href="41467_2018_4968_Article_IEq52.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </inline-formula>. The value 
 <inline-formula id="IEq53" class="inline-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <tex-math id="M139" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$c_{\mathrm{R}}^ \ast$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <math id="M140" class="math">
    <msubsup class="msubsup">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">c</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">R</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mo class="mo">*</mo>
     </mrow>
    </msubsup>
   </math>
   <inline-graphic xlink:href="41467_2018_4968_Article_IEq53.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </inline-formula> declines and 
 <inline-formula id="IEq54" class="inline-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <tex-math id="M141" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$c_{\mathrm{P}}^ \ast$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <math id="M142" class="math">
    <msubsup class="msubsup">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">c</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">P</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mo class="mo">*</mo>
     </mrow>
    </msubsup>
   </math>
   <inline-graphic xlink:href="41467_2018_4968_Article_IEq54.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </inline-formula> increases as 
 <italic class="italic">λ</italic>
 <sub class="sub">R</sub> increases further and when 
 <inline-formula id="IEq55" class="inline-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <tex-math id="M143" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$c_{\mathrm{P}}^ \ast = \frac{{W_{\mathrm{P}}}}{2}$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <math id="M144" class="math">
    <msubsup class="msubsup">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">c</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">P</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mo class="mo">*</mo>
     </mrow>
    </msubsup>
    <mo class="mo">=</mo>
    <mfrac class="mfrac">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <msub class="msub">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">W</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">P</mi>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mn class="mn">2</mn>
     </mrow>
    </mfrac>
   </math>
   <inline-graphic xlink:href="41467_2018_4968_Article_IEq55.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </inline-formula> (equivalent to 
 <inline-formula id="IEq56" class="inline-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <tex-math id="M145" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$\lambda _{\mathrm{R}} = 2\frac{W}{{W_{\mathrm{P}}}}$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <math id="M146" class="math">
    <msub class="msub">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">λ</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">R</mi>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
    <mo class="mo">=</mo>
    <mn class="mn">2</mn>
    <mfrac class="mfrac">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">W</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <msub class="msub">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">W</mi>
       </mrow>
